column3: Has your doctor ever said that you have a heart condition?
Do you feel pain in your chest when you carry out physical activity?
Have you had chest pain when you were not doing physical activity in the past month?
Do you lose your balance because of dizziness or do you ever lose consciousness?

Do you have back/pelvic or other joint problem that could be made worse by a 
change in your physical activity?
Do you have raised blood pressure?
If YES, is this pregnancy related and how is it being treated?
If YES, how is this controlled
Do you know of any other reason that could affect your participation in exercise?
Have you experienced miscarriage in an earlier pregnancy in the past?
Have you experienced other pregnancy complications in the past?
Are you/were you a regular exerciser before becoming pregnant?
Sudden swelling, pain or redness in the calf of one or both leg(s)?
Persistent headaches or problems with headaches?
Sudden swelling of the ankles, hands or face?
Absence of foetal movements after sixth month?
Failure to gain weight after fifth month?
If you have answered YES to any of the above questions, please give details
What physical activity do you intend to do?
Persistent second or third trimester bleeding/placenta praevia?

Uncontrolled type-I diabetes, hypertension or thyroid disease, other serious 
cardiovascular respiratory or systemic diseases?
History of spontaneous abortion or premature labour in previous pregnancies ?
Mild/moderate cardiovascular or respiratory disease (eg, chronic hypertension, asthma) ?
